GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
H 2
HOUSE BILL 186
Committee Substitute Favorable 3/4/25
Short Title: The Stars and Stripes Commitment Act. (Public)
Sponsors:
Referred to:
February 26, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO SCHEDULE RECITATION OF THE PLEDGE OF ALLEGIANCE AT THE
3 BEGINNING OF THE SCHOOL DAY AND TO REQUIRE RECITATION OF THE
4 PLEDGE AT STATE BOARD OF EDUCATION AND GOVERNING BODY MEETINGS.
5 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
6
7 PART I. REQUIRE PLEDGE OF ALLEGIANCE TO BE SCHEDULED AT THE
8 BEGINNING OF THE SCHOOL DAY
9 SECTION 1.(a) G.S. 115C-47(29a) reads as rewritten:
10 "(29a) To Require the Display of the United States and North Carolina Flags, and to
11 Require the Recitation of the Pledge of Allegiance. – Local boards of
12 education shall adopt policies to (i) require the display of the United States
13 and North Carolina flags in each classroom, when available, (ii) require that
14 recitation of the Pledge of Allegiance be scheduled on a daily basis, Pledge of
15 Allegiance, as codified in 4 U.S.C. § 4, be scheduled on a daily basis within
16 one hour of the beginning of the instructional day, and (iii) provide
17 age-appropriate instruction on the meaning and historical origins of the flag
18 and the Pledge of Allegiance. These policies shall not compel any person to
19 stand, salute the flag, or recite the Pledge of Allegiance. If flags are donated
20 or are otherwise available, flags shall be displayed in each classroom."
21 SECTION 1.(b) G.S. 115C-150.12C(23), as enacted by S.L. 2023-10, reads as
22 rewritten:
23 "(23) The Display of the United States and North Carolina Flags and the Recitation
24 of the Pledge of Allegiance. – The board of trustees shall adopt policies to (i)
25 require the display of the United States and North Carolina flags in each
26 classroom when available, (ii) require that recitation of the Pledge of
27 Allegiance be scheduled on a daily basis, Pledge of Allegiance, as codified in
28 4 U.S.C. § 4, be scheduled on a daily basis within one hour of the beginning
29 of the instructional day, and (iii) provide age-appropriate instruction on the
30 meaning and historical origins of the flag and the Pledge of Allegiance. These
31 policies shall not compel any person to stand, salute the flag, or recite the
32 Pledge of Allegiance. If flags are donated or are otherwise available, flags
33 shall be displayed in each classroom."
34 SECTION 1.(c) G.S. 115C-218.80 reads as rewritten:
35 "§ 115C-218.80. Display of the United States and North Carolina flags and the recitation
36 of the Pledge of Allegiance.
