1 A charter school shall (i) display the United States and North Carolina flags in each classroom
2 when available, (ii) require the recitation of the Pledge of Allegiance on a daily basis, Pledge of
3 Allegiance, as codified in 4 U.S.C. § 4, be scheduled on a daily basis within one hour of the
4 beginning of the instructional day, and (iii) provide age-appropriate instruction on the meaning
5 and historical origins of the flag and the Pledge of Allegiance. A charter school shall not compel
6 any person to stand, salute the flag, or recite the Pledge of Allegiance. If flags are donated or are
7 otherwise available, flags shall be displayed in each classroom."
8 SECTION 1.(d) G.S. 115C-238.66 is amended by adding a new subdivision to read:
9 "(23) Recitation of the Pledge of Allegiance. – A regional school shall schedule
10 recitation of the Pledge of Allegiance, as codified in 4 U.S.C. § 4, on a daily
11 basis within one hour of the beginning of the instructional day. A regional
12 school shall not compel any person to stand, salute the flag, or recite the
13 Pledge of Allegiance."
14 SECTION 1.(e) G.S. 116-69.1 reads as rewritten:
15 "§ 116-69.1. Display of the United States and North Carolina flags and the recitation of the
16 Pledge of Allegiance.
17 The school shall (i) display the United States and North Carolina flags in each classroom
18 when available, (ii) require the recitation of the Pledge of Allegiance on a daily basis, Pledge of
19 Allegiance, as codified in 4 U.S.C. § 4, be scheduled on a daily basis within one hour of the
20 beginning of the instructional day, and (iii) provide instruction on the meaning and historical
21 origins of the flag and the Pledge of Allegiance. The school shall not compel any person to stand,
22 salute the flag, or recite the Pledge of Allegiance. If flags are donated or are otherwise available,
23 flags shall be displayed in each classroom."
24 SECTION 1.(f) G.S. 116-235(i) reads as rewritten:
25 "(i) The Display of the United States and North Carolina Flags and the Recitation of the
26 Pledge of Allegiance. – The Board of Trustees shall adopt policies to require (i) the display of
27 the United States and North Carolina flags in each classroom when available, (ii) the recitation
28 of the Pledge of Allegiance on a daily basis, Pledge of Allegiance, as codified in 4 U.S.C. § 4, be
29 scheduled on a daily basis within one hour of the beginning of the instructional day, and (iii) the
30 instruction on the meaning and historical origins of the flag and the Pledge of Allegiance. These
31 policies shall not compel any person to stand, salute the flag, or recite the Pledge of Allegiance.
32 If flags are donated or are otherwise available, flags shall be displayed in each classroom."
33 SECTION 1.(g) G.S. 116-239.8(b) is amended by adding a new subdivision to read:
34 "(26) Display of the United States and North Carolina flags and the recitation of the
35 Pledge of Allegiance. – Laboratory schools shall schedule recitation of the
36 Pledge of Allegiance, as codified in 4 U.S.C. § 4, on a daily basis within one
37 hour of the beginning of the instructional day."
38
39 PART II. REQUIRE RECITATION OF PLEDGE OF ALLEGIANCE AT STATE
40 BOARD OF EDUCATION AND GOVERNING BODY MEETINGS
41 SECTION 2.(a) G.S. 115C-11 reads as rewritten:
42 "§ 115C-11. Organization and internal procedures of Board.
43 …
44 (b) Regular Meetings of Board. – The regular meetings of the Board shall be held each
45 month on a day certain, as determined by the Board. The Board shall determine the hour of the
46 meeting, which may be adjourned from day to day, or to a day certain, until the business before
47 the Board has been completed.
48 (b1) Annual meeting with the State Board of Community Colleges and the Board of
49 Governors of The University of North Carolina. Carolina. – The State Board of Education shall
50 meet with the State Board of Community Colleges and the Board of Governors of The University
51 of North Carolina at least once a year to discuss educational matters of mutual interest and to
Page 2 House Bill 186-Second Edition

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 recommend to the General Assembly such policies as are appropriate to encourage the
2 improvement of public education at every level in this State. The meeting in 1987 and every three
3 years thereafter shall be hosted by the University Board of Governors, the meeting in 1988 and
4 every three years thereafter shall be hosted by the State Board of Education, and the meeting in
5 1989 and every three years thereafter shall be hosted by the State Board of Community Colleges.
6 (b2) Pledge of Allegiance. – Every regular and special meeting of the Board shall begin
7 with recitation of the Pledge of Allegiance, as codified in 4 U.S.C. § 4. This policy shall not
8 compel any person to stand, salute the flag, or recite the Pledge of Allegiance.
9 …."
10 SECTION 2.(b) Article 7B of Chapter 115C of the General Statutes is amended by
11 adding a new section to read:
12 "§ 115C-76.300. Pledge of Allegiance.
13 Every meeting of a governing body of a public school unit shall begin with recitation of the
14 Pledge of Allegiance, as codified in 4 U.S.C. § 4. This policy shall not compel any person to
15 stand, salute the flag, or recite the Pledge of Allegiance."
16
17 PART III. EFFECTIVE DATE
18 SECTION 3. This act is effective when it becomes law and applies beginning with
19 the 2025-2026 school year.
